-- Mercedes Targets 20% U.S. Growth, Schmidt Tells Automotive News
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-01-15T14:57:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-15/mercedes-targets-20-u-s-growth-schmidt-tells-automotive-news.html
Daimler AG (DAI) ’s Mercedes-Benz unit
expects four new compact cars it will introduce over the next
three years to boost sales in the U.S. by 20 percent, Automotive
News Europe said, citing an interview with Joachim Schmidt, the
unit’s head of global sales.  The company is targeting sales in the U.S. of 300,000
vehicles in the “midterm,” Schmidt was cited as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
